(power_internal, power_logic).explanation: Power_logic is a component that contributes to the total internal power consumption of a processor, making logic power a constituent part of internal power;

(power_internal, area_cell_area).explanation: Cell area is a physical design metric that doesn't directly cause or result from internal power consumption, though both may be influenced by design choices;

(power_internal, power_register).explanation: Register power consumption is a specific component that contributes to the overall internal power consumption of the processor;
